column20: Hand-breaded and fried until perfectly crunchy (hence the name). Topped with your choice of Monterey Jack or cheddar cheese and served on a toasted brioche bun with french fries on the side.

Named after the chef who masterminded the perfect breading for this dish and others, these large shrimp are butterflied, hand-breaded and fried until perfectly golden crisp. There&rsquo;s a reason they&rsquo;ve been a menu staple since 1996.

Named for the idyllic seaside town of Bar Harbor, Maine, where lobster bakes are a way of life. Split-roasted petite Maritime lobster tails with shrimp, sea scallops and mussels, piled over a bed of linguini in a garlic and white wine broth.

Don&rsquo;t let our name fool you &mdash;&nbsp;we also make a mean steak, like this 7-ounce sirloin. Lean and packed with flavor, we season it with peppercorns and throw it on the grill until it&rsquo;s cooked how you like it. Served with mashed potatoes plus an extra side.
